Backend Developer
Role Description:
Focuses on server-side logic, APIs, and application infrastructure.

Key Responsibilities:

Develop and maintain server-side application logic.

Design and create RESTful or GraphQL APIs for frontend or other services.

Integrate with databases and external services.

Ensure performance, security, and scalability of the backend systems.

Database Administrator (DBA)
Role Description:
Manages and maintains the database systems to ensure data availability, integrity, and security.

Key Responsibilities:

Design, implement, and maintain database structures.

Optimize database performance through indexing, query tuning, etc.

Ensure data backups, recovery plans, and security measures.

Manage user access and permissions to databases.

Data Engineer
Role Description:
Builds and maintains data pipelines and infrastructure for data collection, storage, and processing.

Key Responsibilities:

Develop ETL/ELT processes to move and transform data.

Build and manage data warehouses/lakes.

Ensure data quality and reliability.

Work with large-scale data systems and big data technologies.





